cs.DL, cs.CE, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper discusses the improvement of mathematical formula rendering on Wikipedia, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) as Wikipedia is a digital library. Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to accessibility (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) for people with special needs. The paper also discusses the technical implementation of the Mathoid software (cs.CE) and the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) to convert input format to MathML.
